comment.body:
@Icf20: 
> there is more, things are not so simple... 
I don't understand this post.  Could you reformulate?  Regarding your other post: it doesn't make sense to say that a bitcoin thief can ignore any compensations imposed by a judge and pretend that the same is not true of a watch thief or someone who stole seven $20s from you.  Anyway, I think that we can all agree that anyone who is deciding to use bitcoin should certainly weigh the risk of theft, user error, volatility, etc. against the gains.
